ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Was there ever a time when you weighed much less than other people thought you ought to weigh?
At that time, had you lost a lot of weight on purpose or was it while you were growing up and you kept your weight down on purpose?
What was your lowest weight at that time?
How tall were you?
How old were you?
INTERVIEWER: Note body frame.
INTERVIEWER: Is lowest weight (question 3) more than table entry for height, gender, and body?
At that time did you still feel fat or did you see yourself as too fat in some ways?
Were you still very much afraid that you could become fat?
If female: Did your periods stop even when you were not pregnant?
If female: Did you miss at least three cycles in a row?
Was there a medical disorder causing your weight loss?
If yes to medical disorder causing weight loss: Specify:
Did your lowered weight follow the use of diet pills, amphetamines, cocaine, or other substances?
If yes to use of substances: Specify:
How old were you the first time your weight was below __? (See weight criterion table for loss of 15%.)
How old were you the last time your weight was below __? (See weight criterion table for loss of 15%.)
Has there been a time in your life when you went on food binges (i.e., rapid consumption of a large amount of food in a discrete period of time, usually less than two hours)?
During these binges were you afraid you could not stop eating, or that your eating was out of control?
Did you have eating binges as often as twice a week for at least three months?
How old were you when you first binged regularly?
How old were you the last time you binged regularly?
Compensatory Behavior: Did you do anything to make up for eating so much, perhaps like making yourself vomit?
Compensatory Behavior: Did you do anything to make up for eating so much, perhaps like taking laxatives or diuretics?
Compensatory Behavior: Did you do anything to make up for eating so much, perhaps like strictly dieting?
Compensatory Behavior: Did you do anything to make up for eating so much, perhaps like .fasting?
Compensatory Behavior: Did you do anything to make up for eating so much, perhaps like exercising a lot?
Compensatory Behavior: Did you do anything to make up for eating so much, perhaps like other?
If Other on compensatory behavior: Specify:
Did you do (Compensatory behavior/s) as often as twice a week for at least 3 months?
At this time when you went on food binges were you a lot more concerned about your weight and/or shape than most people your age?
INTERVIEWER: Are questions 16 and 19g both YES?
Did these episodes of binge eating and (Compensatory behaviors) both occur on average twice a week for at least 3 months?
How old were you when you first binged and (Compensatory behavior/s) regularly?
How old were you the last time you binged and (Compensatory behavior/s) regularly?
Did these episodes of binge eating and (Compensatory behaviors) occur at any time other than during an anorexia episode?
